#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn48.169-178"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 48 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 48 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:0.2"
msgid "15. Punaoghavagga "
msgstr "15. Another Chapter on Floods "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:0.3"
msgid "169–178. punaoghādisutta "
msgstr "169–178. Another Series on Floods, Etc. "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.243, sc1
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, uddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are five higher fetters. "

msgctxt "sn48.169-178:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "sn48.169-178:1.3"
msgid "Rūparāgo, arūparāgo, māno, uddhaccaṃ, avijjā—"
msgstr "Desire for rebirth in the realm of luminous form, desire for rebirth in the formless realm, conceit, restlessness, and ignorance. "

msgctxt "sn48.169-178:1.4"
msgid "imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañcuddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni. "
msgstr "These are the five higher fetters. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:1.5"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya pañcindriyāni bhāvetabbāni. "
msgstr "The five faculties should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters. "

msgctxt "sn48.169-178:1.6"
msgid "Katamāni pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "sn48.169-178:1.7"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddhindriyaṃ bhāveti rāgavinayapariyosānaṃ dosavinayapariyosānaṃ mohavinayapariyosānaṃ. Vīriyindriyaṃ … pe … satindriyaṃ … samādhindriyaṃ … paññindriyaṃ bhāveti rāgavinayapariyosānaṃ dosavinayapariyosānaṃ mohavinayapariyosānaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant develops the faculties of faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom, which culminate in the removal of greed, hate, and delusion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:1.8"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya imāni pañcindriyāni bhāvetabbānī”ti. "
msgstr "These five faculties should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:1.9"
msgid "Oghavaggo sattarasamo. "
msgstr "(To be expanded as in SN 45.171–179, with the above as the final discourse, removal of greed version.) "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:2.1"
msgid "Ogho yogo upādānaṃ, "
msgstr "Floods, bonds, grasping, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:2.2"
msgid "ganthā anusayena ca; "
msgstr "ties, and underlying tendencies, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:2.3"
msgid "Kāmaguṇā nīvaraṇā, "
msgstr "kinds of sensual stimulation, hindrances, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:2.4"
msgid "khandhā oruddhambhāgiyāti. "
msgstr "aggregates, and fetters high and low. "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn48.169-178:2.5"
msgid "Indriyasaṃyuttaṃ catutthaṃ. "
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on the Faculties is the fourth section."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
